allEvents.description: LightSEC 2025 promotes novel research on security, privacy, and trust for applications requiring lightweight security. “Lightweight” refers to constraints on performance metrics like computation, communication, energy, and memory usage, as well as reduced ciphertext and key sizes, and compact zero-knowledge proofs. As emerging cryptographic applications grow across AI, blockchain, IoT, and 5G/6G, ensuring robust yet efficient security becomes critical. LightSEC 2025 welcomes papers on algorithms, protocols, and secure implementations using technologies like homomorphic encryption, zero-knowledge proofs, MPC, blockchain consensus, threshold schemes, and post-quantum cryptography.
